wikipedia_page.main: Nathan Sykes (born 8 September 1974) is an English former professional rugby league footballer who played in the 1990s and 2000s. He played at representative level for England and Yorkshire, and at club level for Moldgreen ARLFC, Castleford Tigers (Heritage № 694) and Featherstone Rovers (captain) (Heritage No. 862), as a prop, or second-row.
